#: ../../docs/user/governance/eight-steps.rst:116
msgid "A few additional points:"
msgstr "补充几点："

#: ../../docs/user/governance/eight-steps.rst:118
msgid ""
"It is currently not possible to change the payment address after the "
"proposal is posted to the blockchain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/governance/eight-steps.rst:121
msgid ""
"To avoid accusations of favouritism and inside trading, Dash Core cannot "
"promote your proposal for you. If your proposal is an integration, reach out"
" to the business development team in advance. Once your product is live, it "
"may be possible to announce it from Dash Core channels."
msgstr ""
"为了避免偏袒和内部交易的指责，Dash "
"Core不能为您推广您的提案。如果您的提案是整合提案，请提前与业务开发团队联系。当您的产品上线后，或许可以从Dash Core 渠道对其进行宣传。"

#: ../../docs/user/governance/eight-steps.rst:127
msgid ""
"If your proposal is for news, promotion or marketing, make sure you "
"synchronise your efforts with major existing organisations such as Dash "
"Force News or marketing firms contracted by Dash Core."
msgstr "如果您的提案用于新闻，推广或营销，确保将您的努力与现有的主要机构，如Dash Force News或Dash Core保持同步。"

#: ../../docs/user/governance/eight-steps.rst:131
msgid ""
"You are responsible for your own planning to hedge against price volatility."
" If your proposal involves significant payments to third parties in fiat "
"currency, reach out to the `Dash Investment Foundation "
"<https://www.dashinvests.org/>`_ in advance for advice on escrow, price "
"maintenance, converting currencies and hedging against volatility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/governance/eight-steps.rst:137
msgid ""
"For the same reason, it is not recommended to request funding for period of "
"longer than three months. Masternodes don't want to see and vote on the same"
" proposal without updates several months in a row, and price volatility "
"makes it a risky proposition both to the network and yourself."
msgstr ""
"出于同样的原因，建议不要申请超过三个月的资金提案。主节点不希望在连续几个月没有更新的情况下查看同一提案并对其进行投票，价格波动使得申请超过三个月的资金提案对网络和您自己来说都是一个冒险。"

#: ../../docs/user/governance/eight-steps.rst:143
msgid ""
"Before entering your budget proposal on the blockchain, check how many "
"proposals already exist for the current budget cycle. If it is likely to "
"become very crowded or if some proposals are requesting a significant "
"portion of the budget, voting is likely to be very competitive with weaker "
"projects being forced out of the budget, even if they collect sufficient "
"votes to pass the 10% threshold. See :ref:`here <understanding-governance>` "
"for more details."
msgstr ""
"在区块链上输入您的预算提案之前，请检查当前预算周期内已经存在了多少提案。如果提案过多可能会变得非常拥挤，或者如果有一些提案的申请占据预算总金额的很大一部分，投票很可能非常有竞争力，即使他们获得足够的票数超过了10%的门槛，也可能被迫踢出预算。请参阅"
" :ref:`此处 <understanding-governance>` 以了解更多详细信息。"
